Code of Conduct

Our Commitment

We are committed to providing a respectful, inclusive, and harassment-free environment for everyone, regardless of experience level, gender, identity, or background.

Expected Behavior

- Be respectful and constructive
- Accept feedback gracefully
- Focus on what is best for the project
- Help others and share knowledge

Unacceptable Behavior

- Harassment, discrimination, or offensive comments
- Personal attacks or toxic behavior
- Spam or irrelevant contributions
- Any form of intimidation or exclusion

Enforcement

Project maintainers are responsible for enforcing this Code of Conduct and may:
- Remove or edit inappropriate content
- Reject contributions
- Temporarily or permanently ban contributors

Reporting Issues

If you experience or witness unacceptable behavior, please report it to:  

contact@properform.app

All reports will be handled confidentially.

---

Scope

This Code of Conduct applies to:
- All project spaces (GitHub, documentation, discussions)
- Any interaction representing the project

